sec.p:
As the thickness of a-Si:H solar cells are only a few hundred nanometers, the substrates will dominate the weight and thickness of the ultimate devices. In this work, we demonstrated flexible solar cells on graphene papers which are much lighter than conventional glass and plastic substrates. Herein, we further compare the weight-specific power density (PW) of devices on different substrates. The PW is defined as the ratio of the output power under standard solar irradiation (AM 1.5 Global spectrum with 1000 W m−2 intensity) to the mass of the solar cell per unit area as expressed by following equation:
